4><p>Your Camera can upload pictures and videos either during an motion alarm or in an time interval. The configuration can be set in the webUI inside the FTP Settings menu ...</p></div></div></a><hr><a href="/Motion_Detection/Router_as_a_FTP_Server/"><div class="articleListItem margin"><div class="articleImage"><amp-img height=100 width=100 layout=responsive src="/images/Landing_Tiles/Wiki_Tiles_MD-Router-FTP-Server_white.png"></amp-img></div><div class="articlePreview"><h4>Local FTP Server</h4><p>Most modern routers now support USB mass storage devices to be plugged in, to be used as Network-Attached-Storage (NAS) ...</p></div></div></a><hr><a href="/Motion_Detection/FTP_Server_Setup/"><div class="articleListItem margin"><div class="articleImage"><amp-img height=100 width=100 layout=responsive src="/images/Landing_Tiles/Wiki_Tiles_MD-FTP-Server_white.png"></amp-img></div><div class="articlePreview"><h4>Filezilla FTP Server</h4><p>Your camera can upload pictures during an alarm event or you can also upload pictures in a defined time period to any kind of FTP server ...</p></div></div></a><hr><a href="/Motion_Detection/Alarm_Server/"><div class="articleListItem margin"><div class="articleImage"><amp-img height=100 width=100 layout=responsive src="/images/Landing_Tiles/Wiki_Tiles_MD-Alarm-Server_white.png"></amp-img></div><div class="articlePreview"><h4>Alarm Server</h4><p>You can use the Alarm Server function to send a http request to a connected server. You can add custom commands to the request to trigger specific actions in the receiving server software ...</p></div></div></a><hr><a href="/Motion_Detection/INSTAR_Cloud/"><div class="articleListItem margin"><div class="articleImage"><amp-img height=100 width=100 layout=responsive src="/images/Landing_Tiles/Wiki_Tiles_MD-INSTAR-Cloud_white.png"></amp-img></div><div class="articlePreview"><h4>INSTAR Cloud</h4><p>An overview over our - optional - online recording platform for your INSTAR IP camera. ...</p></div></div